The Issue: Brute-force login attempts are going unnoticed.

The Solution: Writing a custom Snort rule to trigger an alert.

 IDS-Snort-Rule-Lab.md
# Melissa Rachel Wozney - Detection Lab
# Rule: Alert on any TCP traffic from external network to internal port 22 (SSH).

alert tcp $EXTERNAL_NET any -> $HOME_NET 22 (msg:"SSH Brute Force Attempt Detected"; sid:1000001; rev:1;)

# Result: This rule provides real-time visibility into unauthorized access attempts.
